
[1]vindicate

   VIN'DICATE, v.t. [L. vindico.]

   1. To defend; to justify; to support or maintain as true or correct,
   against denial, censure or objections.

   When the respondent denies any proposition, the opponent must vindicate
   it.

   Laugh where we must, be candid where we can; but vindicate the ways of
   God to man.

   2. To assert; to defend with success; to maintain; to prove to be just
   or valid; as, to vindicate a claim or title.

   3. To defend with arms, or otherwise; as, to vindicate our rights.

   4. to avenge; to punish; as a war to vindicate or punish infidelity.

   God is more powerful to exact subjection and to vindicate rebellion.

   [This latter use is entirely obsolete.]
